Configuration
Key parameters in config.py:

python
THRESHOLD_RESOLUTION = (35, 35)  # Minimum acceptable resolution
SUPER_RES_FACTOR = 4             # Super-resolution factor k
RESNET_FEATURES_DIM = 2062       # F vector dimensions
FACENET_FEATURES_DIM = 128       # E vector dimensions
EYE_BLINK_THRESHOLD = 0.3        # EAR threshold for blink detection
Performance Metrics
The system calculates standard biometric metrics:

FAR (False Acceptance Rate)

FRR (False Rejection Rate)

TPR (True Positive Rate, Sensitivity)

TNR (True Negative Rate, Specificity)

ACC (Accuracy)

Requirements
Python 3.8+

PyTorch 2.0+

OpenCV 4.8+

dlib 19.24+

facenet-pytorch 2.5+

Datasets
The system is designed to work with:

LFW (Labeled Faces in the Wild) - for super-resolution training

VGGFace2 or CASIA-WebFace - for feature extractor training

NUAA, Replay-Attack, CASIA-FASD - for liveness detection training

References
Based on the paper:
"FaSIVA: Facial signature for identification, verification and authentication of persons"
by Elie Tagne Fute, Lionel Landry Sop Deffo, Emmanuel Toney

